\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces Per-head recovery (mean $\pm $ SEM, $n{=}8$) at the three layers around the L=20 lesion. \textbf  {L=16}: flat distribution, no head dominates. \textbf  {L=20}: head 10 stands out at $2.5\times $ the next head, and is the only large-effect head at any patched $(\ell , h)$ cell tested. \textbf  {L=24}: recovery is essentially zero across all heads. The L20H10 dominance is what allows us to compress the lesion description from ``a mid-network circuit'' to a two-head circuit (L20H10 $\to $ L36H31).}}{16}{figure.caption.36}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:phase7b-headzoom}{{9}{16}{Per-head recovery (mean $\pm $ SEM, $n{=}8$) at the three layers around the L=20 lesion. \textbf {L=16}: flat distribution, no head dominates. \textbf {L=20}: head 10 stands out at $2.5\times $ the next head, and is the only large-effect head at any patched $(\layerL , h)$ cell tested. \textbf {L=24}: recovery is essentially zero across all heads. The L20H10 dominance is what allows us to compress the lesion description from ``a mid-network circuit'' to a two-head circuit (L20H10 $\to $ L36H31)}{figure.caption.36}{}}
